<!DOCTYPE html>
%html
  %head
    %title Codebreaker
    %link{ rel: 'shortcut icon', href: 'img/favicon/favicon.ico', type: 'image/x-icon' }
    -# %link{ rel: "stylesheet", href: "https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.2/css/bootstrap.min.css", integrity: "sha384-Smlep5jCw/wG7hdkwQ/Z5nLIefveQRIY9nfy6xoR1uRYBtpZgI6339F5dgvm/e9B", crossorigin: "anonymous"}
    %link{ rel: 'stylesheet', href: '/css/application.css', type: 'text/css' }
  %body
    .container
     
      = render 'login_form'
      -# = render 'game_session'
      
      -# Modal for RULES
      %a.modal-trigger{:href => "#modal_rules"} Rules
      #modal_rules.modal
        .modal__dialog
          %section.modal__content
            %header.modal__header
              %h2.modul__title Rules
              %a.modal__close{:href => "#"}
            .modal__body
              %p.modal__text
                The code-breaker then gets some number of chances to break the code.In each turn, the code-breaker makes a guess of four numbers.The code-maker then marks the guess with up to four + and - signs.
                %br
                  You have #{ATTEMPTS} attempts attempts and game answers with up to four pluses and minuses.
                  %ul
                    %li
                      + (plus) indicates an exact match:
                      %br
                        one of the numbers in the guess is the same as one of the numbers in the secret code and in the same position.
                      %li
                        \- (minus) indicates a number match:
                        %br
                          one of the numbers in the guess is the same as one of the numbers in the secret code but in a different position.
                        %h3 Tips  Tricks
                        HINTS: type 'h' and game will show one  number from code to you
                    %footer.modal__footer
                      %a.modal__link{:href => "/"} Ok, I've read